Description: Handle of pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.51, 10, although there is a strong possibility that it may be equated with British Museum 1925,0119.105, or, less likely, 2011,5003.305. Parallels from Miletus are published by G. Joehrens. 'Amphorenstempel aus den Grabungen in Milet 1899-2007', Arch.Anz. 2009, 213.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0068)
